value.0: Welcome tae my shop. Would ye like to see me wares?
Aye... here's a little for yer trouble. I don't pay so much for em though, deer hides is more useful ye know.
Very good. Here's your reward.

A fine specimen *takes the carcass, skins and dresses it, wrapping the skinned carcass and passing it back to you* 'ere's yer pay, with ma thanks. The meat be yours - butcher be up east o' thae market square, if'n ye want tae sell it.

No' me, no. ...then again, if'n ye don't mind travellin' a bit, out east past Koart and afore ye get tae Kingsbay, ye'll find O'Malley. There's another man there who be sellin' leathers - old as thae hills he is. 'e were my master when I were but an apprentice.

'e likes tae patronise me by buyin' some o' my wares every month. If'n ye go talk tae him 'e might give ye a job pickin some up for 'im.
*a wry chuckle* nae, 'e wouldn't like that. That'd be 'is old 'pprentice gettin' persumptuous. If ye talk tae him 'e might give ye the job. Then ye can come back 'ere and I'll give ye the goods.

Aye, I'll pay ye - an more than tha' tannery or them hunters at O'Malley will pay ye, at that. Bring me tha carcass o' a dead deer - or jus' the hides, if'n ye've already had it skinned by thae butcher, an' I'll pay ye for thae hide.

If ye give me the whole carcass, I'll give ye the meat back too fer you tae take tae the butcher's, they'll pay ye for the meat.

The butcher'll skin thae dead deer for ye as well, an should give ye the hides tha' ye can then bring ta me. Or ye can come tae me first, it don't matter so much... though I be better at thae skinnin', o' course.
There be a butcher 'ere in Corwell, east o' thae market square. There be one in O'Malley too, though 'e won't give ye so much coin as thae city butchers, ye ken.
I'm no hunter. Ye'd be better askin' at that hunter's camp near O'Malley. They  might be willin' tae give ye a hint.
*eyes you* blimey, yer a right foreigner ain't ye. Cantrev O'Malley, it be east o' here, on thae Corwell road. Thae Guards'll give ye directions if'n ye ask nicely.

Ah, fer ol' Arad eh? Aye I have his order here. Ol' codger still thinks 'e's needin ta look out fer me does 'e? *chuckles and hands over a large bundle* Careful with those eh, fine wares all.

Tell the ol' boy all's well, an' I'll have 'is next order ready as usual in a month eh.
I have these wolf hides, will you pay me for them? *hand over a wolf hide*
I have something else to ask you about
Thanks *leave*
I have another *hand over another wolf hide*
No, thanks.
*hefting some deer hides* Here on business. Butcher already skinned my take, so here's the hides for you *give the tanner your deer hides*
Thanks *leave*
Got another here! *give the tanner another hide*
*lugging a dead deer* Here on business. I'll want the meat back, you can keep the rest.
Got another one here! *give another deer carcass to the tanner*
Thanks very much *leave*
Hello. Do you have any work for a wandering traveller, by any chance?
Can't I just take the package from you now and deliver it to him?
Can I have a look at your wares?
Whatever, can't be bothered *leave*
*sigh* fine. I'll stop in on the leather shop when I'm next in O'Malley.
I'm going deer hunting. Will you pay me for any dead deer or hides that I bring back?
What was that about a butcher?
I see *leave*
Where's the butcher?
All right, thanks.
I see. Where's the best place for hunting by the way?
What's this O'Malley place you keep going on about?
Fine, I'll get more information from the guards.
All right, thanks
Amazing! I'm going to go and kill some cute baby deer, and I'll be right back!
I'm here about a package of goods for some old bloke over in O'Malley.
Thanks, I'll take these back to Aran right away *leave*
Yes. I'd like to see what you have for sale.
